thursday tour rodin and america influence and adaptation 1876 1936 events at stanford thursday tour rodin and america influence and adaptation 1876 1936 facebook twitter email print add to calendar auguste rodin the most famous sculptor of his day not only appealed to sophisticated american collectors but also had a profound influence on american artists beginning in the 1890s and persisting for decades after rodin's death in 1917 this exhibition is the first to examine the scope of this influence analyzing the impact of both his work itself and his ideas on sculptors such as malvina hoffman and lorado taft as well as on artists working in two dimensions such as the photographer edward steichen and the painter georgia o keeffe when ongoing every week from october 6 2011 through january 1 2012 12 15 pm approximate duration of 1 hour s where cantor arts center just off palm drive at museum way and lomita drive map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags tour international arts contact 723 3469 admission open wed sun 11am 5pm thursdays until 8pm admission is free closed monday and tuesday no tour on thanksgiving day permalink http events stanford edu events 285 28587 more info last modified october 13 2011
